A: The error you're seeing is because you're trying to start an activity from a service, which is not allowed. Services are meant to run in the background and perform long-running operations, not to interact with the user interface.

You should start your service from your MainActivity and then let it start a new activity when it's ready.

Here's how you can modify your code:
MainActivity:
public class MainActivity extends AppCompatActivity {

    @Override
    protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
        super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
        setContentView(R.layout.activity_main);
    }

    public void start_clicked(View view) {
        Intent my_intent = new Intent(this, BackgroundService.class);
        startService(my_intent); // use startService instead of startActivity
    }
}

BackgroundService:
public class BackgroundService extends Service {
    private Socket my_socket;

    public BackgroundService() {
        try {
            my_socket = new Socket(ip, 5000);
        } catch(Exception e){
            // handle exception
        }
    }

    @Override
    public int onStartCommand(Intent intent, int flags, int startId) {
        try {
            DataOutputStream my_stream = new DataOutputStream(my_socket.getOutputStream());
            my_stream.write(121);
        } catch(Exception e){
            // handle exception
        }
